          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Grade 3 proteinuria, and the presence of hyaline and fatty cast in urine suggest the diagnosis of nephrotic syndrome.\nMost common cause of nephrotic syndrome in a child is minimal change disease ( not IgA nephropathy or Alport syndrome)\nIn minimal change disease there is no deposition of immune reactants (immunoglobulin or complement), and serum complement levels are normal."
