          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "→ Apart from A< B and O, RBC of type O contains large amount of another antigen called H substance.\n→ H substance is genetically different from ABO, but is a precursor of A and B antigens.\n→ An O group individual who inherits A or B genes, but fails to inherit H gene from either parent is called Oh phenotype or Bombay blood group."
