          "explanation": "Answer: c) Coumarin is antagonizing vitamin K reductase necessary for production of factors II, VII, IX and X* Vitamin K is necessary for production of factors II, VII, IX, and X. Coumarin will antagonize vitamin K reductase and can result in the bloody stool after poisoning* Irritation of bowels is possible, but it wouldn't cause bleeding.* DIC is not caused by coumarin based poisons.",
