          "explanation": "Hypofibrinogemia Patient will low level of fibrinogen Factor IX deficiency Clotting factor deficiency APTT value is abnormal Rare in females Immune thrombocytopenia Platelet count will be low Von Willebrand disease Most common cause of inherited bleeding disorder One of the common causes of pubey menorrhagia PT, platelet count and fibrinogen levels will be normal APTT will be normal or mildly increased in type 1, types 2A, 2B, 2M APTT will be significantly increased in type 2N, type 3 VWF antigen and activity will be reduced leading to bleeding symptoms Function of VWF - Adhesion of platelets and increase half life of factor 8",
