          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "In CLL, the blood contains large numbers of small round lymphocytes with scant cytoplasm (fragile). Some of these cells are usually disrupted in the process of making smears, producing so-called smudge cells",
          "hint": "Topic: Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia"
