          "explanation": "Siuins They are a family of NAD-dependent protein deacetylases. There are at least 7 types They have non-redundant functions designed to adapt bodily functions to various environmental stresses, including Food deprivation and DNA damage. Functions:- These include proteins that inhibit metabolic activity Reduce apoptosis Stimulate protein folding Inhibit the harmful effects of oxygen free radicals. Siuins also increase insulin sensitivity and glucose metabolism, and may be targets for the treatment of diabetes.",
