          "explanation": "Complications of bacterial pneumonia include pleuritis (extension of inflammation to the pleural surface), pleural effusion, pyothorax (infection of pleural effusion), pulmonary abscess and pulmonary fibrosis. Empyema is a loculated collection of pus with fibrous walls that follows the spread of bacterial infection to the pleural space. All of the other choices are possible routes of spread, but do not describe empyema.",
